definition: (bird species of China) whooper swan (Cygnus cygnus)
big/huge/large/major/great/wide/deep/older (than)/oldest/eldest/greatly/very much/(dialect) father/father's elder or younger brother

sentences.english: The team's mascot is a giant swan .
sentences.chinese: 這個隊的吉祥物是隻大天鵝。

sentences.english: Village arrange a fixed time feeding in large swan.
sentences.chinese: 村裏安排專人在固定時間餵食大天鵝。

sentences.english: The whooper swan is a bird to inspire flights of fancy.
sentences.chinese: 美麗的大天鵝，給人們帶來無限的遐想。

sentences.english: A photographer captures the grace and poetry of the whooper swan.
sentences.chinese: 攝影師鏡頭中的大天鵝，嫺靜文雅，充滿詩意。
